---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import FirstSteps from '../components/FirstSteps.astro';

const questions = [
	'Does it seem like your words are never really heard?',
	'Has a secret been uncovered that feels unrecoverable?',
	'Do you feel unappreciated or not cared about?',
	'Do arguments end, only to start again with the same results?',
	'Are you headed for separation or divorce?',
];
---

<Layout
	title="Online Couples Counseling in Colorado | Custom Counseling"
	description="Structured online couples counseling — a focused 8–12 week approach to rebuild communication and connection. For couples anywhere in Colorado."
>
	<PageHero
		heading="Online Couples Counseling in Colorado"
		subhead="A confidential mediator can be the difference maker you've been looking for."
	/>

	<section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-14 sm:px-6 md:py-20">
		<div class="prose-site text-lg">
			<p>
				When couples call, it often goes like this: <em
					>"I think we're both burned out. It's like we're roommates."</em
				>
			</p>
			<p>Sound familiar? Ask yourself:</p>
		</div>

		<ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
			{
				questions.map((q) => (
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<span aria-hidden="true" class="mt-2.5 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-clay-400" />
						<span class="text-lg">{q}</span>
					</li>
				))
			}
		</ul>

		<div class="prose-site mt-12 text-lg">
			<h2 class="text-3xl">A focused 8–12 week approach</h2>
			<p>
				I typically spend <strong>8 to 12 weeks</strong> working with a couple. It is not an
				open-ended dialogue where we rehash the same issues over and over. The focus is to move
				you out of reactivity and into conscious responses to each other's needs.
			</p>
			<p>
				It works best when both partners are willing to fight <strong>for</strong> each other.
				Otherwise one person's growth can feel to the other like being left behind.
			</p>
			<h2 class="text-3xl">How it works over video</h2>
			<p>
				Most couples join together from home on one screen. Separate devices work too. We'll set
				it up in whatever way gets you both talking.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<FirstSteps />
</Layout>
